Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens; roughly chop whites. Quarter @Lemon{1%unit}. Trim and halve @Button Mushrooms{4%ounce}(trimmed and halved, quarter any large mushrooms).

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @OLD BAY® Seasoning{1%unit}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Roast on top rack, flipping halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @Shredded Red Cabbage{4%ounce}, scallion greens, @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, @Sugar{1%teaspoon}, and juice from one lemon wedge. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

> Use 2 tsp sugar for 4 servings, and juice two lemon wedges for 4 servings.

In a second medium bowl, combine @Mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @Dijon Mustard{4%teaspoon}, scallion whites, juice from one lemon wedge, and @Hot Sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste.

In a third medium bowl, whisk together @Tempura Batter{82%g}, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining Old Bay Seasoning, @cold water{1/3%cup}, and a big pinch of @Salt{}. (TIP: If mixture is too thick, add more water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches a pancake-batter-like consistency.) Stir mushrooms into batter until fully coated.

Rinse @Shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Divide batter between 2 #medium bowls{}. Toss mushrooms in one bowl and shrimp in the other.

Heat a 1/3-inch layer of @Cooking Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the pan, use #tongs{} to add coated mushrooms in a single layer. TIP: Work in batches if necessary.

Cook until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on first side and ~{1-2%minutes} on second side. Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Season with @Salt{}.

After frying mushrooms, heat another 1/3-inch layer of oil in same pan. Working in batches if needed, add shrimp in a single layer. Cook until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate. Season with @Salt{}.

While mushrooms cook, cut @Demi-Baguette{2%unit} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through.

Toast, cut sides up, (place directly on oven rack or use a baking sheet) until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Spread cut sides of baguettes with remoulade; fill with mushrooms, @Sliced Dill Pickle{1%unit}, and as much slaw as you like.

> Add shrimp to sandwiches.

Divide sandwiches and fries between plates. Serve with any remaining slaw, any remaining remoulade, and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> If you've got some on hand, serve ketchup or malt vinegar with your fries!